      "message": "this isn\u0027t a great pattern. Please consider starting a txn in the callsite without a txn, and removing L202-206\n\nafter reading this CL more: are we doing this only because tests didn\u0027t start a txn? I think test code should influence prod code as least as possible, and ideally the code that runs in the production (this func starts a txn) is same as we run in tests (this func doesn\u0027t start a txn)",
