        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-17T06:47:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if this function returns an appstatus w/ internal, the intention is clearer, and this functions will return only single kind of errors; appstatus.\n\nif this returns errors.Annotate() then wouldn\u0027t the original RBECAS error details to be included in the response sent to clients? I don\u0027t think the storage backend error with details will be useful to clients. There is nothing they can do with the information.",
      "parentUuid": "3eba97b0_b7297cf2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 251,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 258,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "c2aa54325a483c053abf0799aa1ad195b195b61e",
