      },
      "lineNbr": 273,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-17T06:47:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We validate the total size of a user request before reaching this point.\nAt this point, if rbecas.BatchUpdateBlobs() ever returns INVALID_ARGUMENT, it means that MaxBatchCreateArtifactSize at L42 is bigger than the actual limit enforced in RBE-CAS.\n\nAs we agreed on https://crbug.com/1177213#c4, we just choose a size limit that is certainly lower than the actual limit in RBE-CAS. Then, this error should never happen. If it happens ever, it means either of the following happened.\n\n1) Our assumption was wrong.\n2) The limit is hard-coded in the current RBECAS server implementation, and never be changed. For some reasons, RBECAS team decided to change the limit to a lower value.\n\nThe error shouldn\u0027t be invalid argument, as this is clearly a server-side error.",
      "parentUuid": "1fef71ad_c068656c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 273,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 273,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "c2aa54325a483c053abf0799aa1ad195b195b61e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
